00:55.066 --> 00:57.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
UNIDENTIFIED MALE: He's
one of the primary sonic
architects of rock and roll.

00:57.133 --> 01:01.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, he helped establish this
art form that we all know and
love, and that really sort

01:01.533 --> 01:02.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of took over the world.

01:02.533 --> 01:04.066 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

01:04.066 --> 01:08.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour".

01:11.800 --> 01:15.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:15.366 --> 01:20.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: President Trump faced
dramatically different crowds
as he made his way across

01:22.566 --> 01:24.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Europe today.

01:24.600 --> 01:29.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
His second overseas trip began
in Poland, before he moved
on to Hamburg, Germany, the

01:30.633 --> 01:34.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
site of the summit of
leaders of the major
industrialized nations.

01:34.900 --> 01:36.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Special correspondent
Ryan Chilcote reports.

01:36.833 --> 01:39.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEOTAPE)

01:39.266 --> 01:41.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE, PBS NEWSHOUR
SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT
(voice-over): President
Trump kicked off his

01:41.366 --> 01:46.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
second trip to Europe by doing
something he was criticized
for not doing on his first:

01:47.533 --> 01:49.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
offering America's full
commitment to the NATO alliance.

01:49.666 --> 01:53.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TRUMP: The United States has
demonstrated not merely with
words but with its actions

01:55.766 --> 02:00.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that we stand firmly
behind Article 5, the
mutual defense commitment.

02:02.933 --> 02:06.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Words are easy but
actions are what matters.

02:06.533 --> 02:11.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
CHILCOTE: Mr. Trump was
addressing a friendly
crowd of some 15,000
in Warsaw, Poland, some

02:13.633 --> 02:18.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the spectators bused
in by the country's
center-right governing party.

02:18.033 --> 02:22.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
To the delight of Poles
concerned about Russia,
their neighbor to the
east, he declared the

02:22.700 --> 02:25.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
West would triumph over
its many adversaries.

02:25.766 --> 02:30.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TRUMP: The fundamental question
of our time is whether the
West has the will to survive.

02:33.433 --> 02:38.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I declare today for the
world to hear that the West
will never, ever be broken.

02:40.466 --> 02:45.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Our values will prevail, our
people will thrive, and our
civilization will triumph.

02:48.600 --> 02:53.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHILCOTE: The president, though,
reiterated criticism of some
NATO allies in Western Europe

02:54.766 --> 02:57.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
for not committing more
to defense spending.

02:57.400 --> 03:01.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mr. Trump also offered his
most forceful condemnation
yet of Russia, just a
day before his meeting

03:02.700 --> 03:04.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with President Vladimir Putin.

03:04.766 --> 03:09.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TRUMP: We urge Russia to cease
its destabilizing activities in
Ukraine and elsewhere and its

03:12.600 --> 03:17.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
support for hostile regimes,
including Syria and Iran, and
to instead join the community

03:19.333 --> 03:21.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of responsible nations.

03:21.533 --> 03:26.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHILCOTE: Hours earlier, at a
press conference with Poland's
president, though, Mr. Trump

03:26.366 --> 03:30.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
skirted questions about Russian
meddling in the 2016 election.

03:30.133 --> 03:35.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
REPORTER: Will you once and for
all, yes or no, definitively
say that Russia interfered

03:35.066 --> 03:37.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with the 2016 election?

03:37.533 --> 03:41.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TRUMP: Well, I think it
was Russia and I think
it could've been other
people and other countries.

03:42.400 --> 03:44.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It could've been a lot
of people interfered.

03:44.000 --> 03:46.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Nobody really knows, nobody
really knows for sure.

03:46.633 --> 03:50.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
CHILCOTE: Mr. Trump also
cast blame on former
President Barack Obama.

03:50.733 --> 03:54.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TRUMP: I think what happened is
that he thought Hillary Clinton
was going to win the election

03:54.866 --> 03:57.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and he said, let's not
do anything about it.

03:57.266 --> 04:00.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Had he thought the other
way, he would have done
something about it.

04:00.200 --> 04:04.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHILCOTE: President Trump
then flew to Hamburg,
Germany for the G20 Summit.

04:04.566 --> 04:06.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There he met German
Chancellor Angela Merkel.

04:06.933 --> 04:11.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The two have publicly tussled
on a variety of issues including
trade and climate change.

04:13.933 --> 04:18.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
All the while the "welcome to
hell" protest, its actual title,
was already under way, turning

04:19.800 --> 04:21.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
violent almost immediately.

04:21.833 --> 04:26.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Thousands of protesters clashed
with police in riot gear who
used water cannons to disperse

04:27.033 --> 04:28.566 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
crowds.

04:28.566 --> 04:31.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Others rushed demonstrators,
tackling them to the ground.

04:31.033 --> 04:33.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEOTAPE)

04:33.000 --> 04:34.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHILCOTE: President Trump's
most important meeting
is, of course, tomorrow.

04:34.933 --> 04:38.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That will be his first
ever meeting with the
president of Russia -- Judy.

04:38.933 --> 04:41.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: And, Ryan,
you've covered the Kremlin.

04:41.866 --> 04:46.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How do you think Mr. Putin is
going to react to what President
Trump had to say today about

04:48.033 --> 04:50.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Russia's interference
in last year's election?

04:50.000 --> 04:54.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHILCOTE: Well, look, I don't
think that President Putin
will like those remarks.

04:54.266 --> 04:59.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At the same time, I think in
a way he will appreciate that
they were made in Poland and

05:00.833 --> 05:05.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
not here at the G20 Summit, not
alongside the Russian president.

05:07.766 --> 05:12.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, they're well
aware that President Trump
is optically challenged.

05:14.466 --> 05:18.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It will be very difficult
for him to say something
pro-Russian at this point.

05:20.600 --> 05:24.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They feel that, at this point,
it would be very difficult
for him to really achieve much

05:26.000 --> 05:30.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
when it comes to improving the
Russian-American relationship.

05:30.166 --> 05:32.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They just don't want to
see it get any worse.

05:32.866 --> 05:37.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I think they'll think
that he was sort of speaking
to the crowd, speaking to the

05:39.766 --> 05:43.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
parlor, if you will, and what
really matters is what President
Trump tells them in that

05:45.100 --> 05:49.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
- - or tells President
Putin in that room when
it comes to policy, and
namely what President

05:51.600 --> 05:54.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Putin is hoping is two
things, that one, President
Trump will perhaps listen
to some of the issues

05:56.266 --> 06:00.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he has with the Ukrainian
side, when it comes to
Russia's conflict in Ukraine,

06:02.800 --> 06:06.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and secondly, President Putin
will be hoping that he can use
Russia's precedence in Syria,

06:08.000 --> 06:11.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what Russia is doing in Syria
as a bridge to the United
States, find some kind of common

06:13.900 --> 06:17.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ground, encourage President
Trump to pursue for example
Islamic State in Syria together

06:18.633 --> 06:20.666 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with Syria.

06:20.666 --> 06:23.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
That is a whole lot
of challenges but that
has always been the
Russians' big hope that

06:23.566 --> 06:28.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they can team up with the United
States or at least the lower
the level, the temperature

06:28.000 --> 06:32.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the relationship by
working together in Syria.

06:32.233 --> 06:35.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
WOODRUFF: Ryan Chilcote
reporting for us from
Hamburg, thank you.

06:35.633 --> 06:37.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
CHILCOTE: Thank you.

06:37.733 --> 06:41.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: And we'll hear more
about President Trump's visit
to Poland and Germany, after

06:41.566 --> 06:43.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the news summary.

06:43.566 --> 06:47.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the day's other news,
world powers are jousting over
how to handle North Korea's

06:47.633 --> 06:50.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
test of an intercontinental
ballistic missile.

06:50.366 --> 06:55.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The president of China,
Pyongyang's closest ally,
called for restraint.

06:55.233 --> 07:00.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In Europe earlier today,
President Trump says
he still hopes that
Beijing can help resolve

07:02.133 --> 07:04.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the North Koreans'
tensions, but said the U.S.
has a range of options.

07:04.066 --> 07:05.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

07:05.566 --> 07:07.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TRUMP: I don't like to talk
about what I have planned.

07:07.933 --> 07:12.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But I have some pretty
severe things that we
are thinking about.

07:12.466 --> 07:14.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That does not mean we
are going to do them.

07:14.300 --> 07:16.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I don't draw red lines.

07:16.800 --> 07:21.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's a shame that they're
behaving this way, but
they are behaving in
a very, very dangerous

07:23.233 --> 07:26.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
manner and something will
have to be done about it.

07:26.666 --> 07:28.766 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

07:28.766 --> 07:31.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Meanwhile, there's
word that it was Russia that
blocked the U.N. Security

07:31.333 --> 07:35.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Council's approval of
a statement strongly
condemning that launch.

07:35.633 --> 07:40.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The Trump administration
has renewed its offer
to cooperate with Russia
over the Syria conflict.

07:43.166 --> 07:46.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a statement last night,
Secretary of State Rex
Tillerson said the U.S.
is open to coordinating

07:47.600 --> 07:50.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
on no fly-zones in Syria.

07:50.100 --> 07:54.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Later, State Department
spokeswoman Heather Nauert said
the broader American strategy

07:54.633 --> 07:55.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
remains the same.

07:55.633 --> 07:57.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

07:57.733 --> 08:00.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HEATHER NAUERT, STATE
DEPARTMENT SPOKESWOMAN:
If our two countries
can establish stability

08:00.333 --> 08:02.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on the ground, we believe
that will lay a foundation
for progress on the
political settlement

08:02.833 --> 08:04.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of Syria's future.

08:04.933 --> 08:08.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The policy has not changed,
some of the words and some of
the phrasing may have changed

08:10.966 --> 08:13.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at this point, but overall,
it's just one of a series of
options that the United States

08:13.900 --> 08:14.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
will now consider.

08:14.900 --> 08:16.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

08:16.933 --> 08:19.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: For his part, Russia's
foreign minister, Sergey Lavrov,
asked for more information

08:19.533 --> 08:24.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on the proposal, but said
cooperation is, quote, a
step in the right direction.

08:26.466 --> 08:29.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A survey commissioned by the
State Department shows diplomats
are frustrated and confused

08:30.800 --> 08:32.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
by the Trump administration.

08:32.766 --> 08:36.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"The Wall Street Journal"
first reported on the document,
which was released to State

08:36.366 --> 08:38.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Department employees yesterday.

08:38.533 --> 08:43.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It comes as the president seeks
drastic cuts to diplomatic
and development funding.

08:45.366 --> 08:49.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Separately, the State Department
is saying the U.S. refugee
admissions program won't

08:49.200 --> 08:51.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
be suspended until next week.

08:51.766 --> 08:56.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
After the Supreme Court
upheld part of the Trump
administration's travel
ban, re-settlement

08:56.666 --> 09:01.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
agencies were told to
schedule refugee arrivals
only through today.

09:03.633 --> 09:06.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it's been announced that
they can now continue until July
12th, when refugee admissions

09:07.866 --> 09:09.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
are expected to hit
their cap of 50,000.

09:09.866 --> 09:14.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The government ethics director
who has prodded the Trump
administration over conflicts of

09:15.533 --> 09:17.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
interest is resigning.

09:17.233 --> 09:22.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Walter Shaub is stepping
down months before his
term was set to expire.

09:24.133 --> 09:27.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In a statement on Twitter, he
said: It has become clear to
me that we need improvements

09:27.300 --> 09:29.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to the existing ethics program.

09:29.733 --> 09:34.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This follows the resignation
of a top Justice Department
official over ethics concerns.

09:36.700 --> 09:41.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Democratic attorneys general
in 18 states and the District
of Columbia are suing Education

09:43.300 --> 09:47.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Secretary Betsy DeVos,
over her delay of rules
on for-profit colleges.

09:50.033 --> 09:53.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The lawsuit demands the
implementation of the
rules created under the
Obama administration.

09:55.300 --> 09:58.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're meant to cancel the
student-loan debt of people
defrauded by those schools.

10:00.466 --> 10:04.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Illinois House of
Representatives has voted to
over-ride the governor's veto of

10:04.866 --> 10:06.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a budget package.

10:06.933 --> 10:10.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It means that Illinois
will have its first annual
spending plan since 2015.

10:12.233 --> 10:15.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is the longest
state fiscal crisis since
the Great Depression.

10:15.466 --> 10:20.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lawmakers voted 71 to 42 to
approve the $36 billion budget
plan, which is funded with

10:21.866 --> 10:25.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
a $5 billion income
tax increase.

10:25.800 --> 10:30.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On Wall Street today, stocks
had their biggest drop in more
than six weeks, amid signs that

10:31.533 --> 10:33.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
hiring has slowed.

10:33.166 --> 10:37.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The Dow Jones Industrial
Average lost 158 points
to close at 21320.

10:39.366 --> 10:44.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Nasdaq fell 61 points, and
the S&amp;P 500 dropped almost 23.

10:46.200 --> 10:50.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
what's behind protests and
reaction in Europe to President

10:51.933 --> 10:55.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trump's visit today, Hobby Lobby
accused of illegally importing
artifacts, a city in New

10:57.066 --> 11:01.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
York that sees refugees
as a boon for economic
development, and much more.

11:07.866 --> 11:09.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(MUSIC)

11:09.900 --> 11:14.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: As we've heard,
President Trump has voiced,
at times, contradictory views

11:16.766 --> 11:20.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on the U.S.'s relationship
with its European
allies and with Russia.

11:20.900 --> 11:25.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
To parse out where things stand
after the first full day of
the president's trip abroad

11:25.866 --> 11:29.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and the road ahead, we
turn to Paula Dobriansky.

11:29.600 --> 11:34.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She was under secretary
of state for democracy
and global affairs
during the George W. Bush

11:35.533 --> 11:37.666 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
administration.

11:37.666 --> 11:41.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's now a senior fellow
at Harvard University and
she joins us from Warsaw.

11:41.233 --> 11:46.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Karen Donfried was special
assistant to the president and
senior director for European

11:48.266 --> 11:52.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
affairs on the National
Security Council during
the Obama administration.

11:52.133 --> 11:57.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
She's now the president
of the German Marshall
Fund in the U.S., an
organization which seeks

11:58.233 --> 12:00.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to straighten
relations with Europe.

12:00.266 --> 12:02.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And we welcome both
of you to the program.

12:02.333 --> 12:05.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Paula Dobriansky, to
you first in Warsaw.

12:05.533 --> 12:10.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Overall, what would you say
the message is from President
Trump that's come across to

12:11.266 --> 12:13.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
his European listeners?

12:13.766 --> 12:17.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL DOBRIANSKY, FORMER
GEORGE W. BUSH STATE
DEPARTMENT OFFICIAL:
Well, the primary message

12:19.633 --> 12:22.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was that European security
matters to us greatly,
that towards that end that
the forward deployment

12:25.000 --> 12:28.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of our troops on the
border matter greatly.

12:28.266 --> 12:32.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They reassure not just the
Poles but the neighborhood.

12:32.166 --> 12:37.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And also the important of the
alliance, that Article 5, our
collective defense is crucial

12:39.100 --> 12:42.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and toward that end, that
alliance has played an
important role in the past.

12:42.566 --> 12:45.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It does now and it
will in the future.

12:45.033 --> 12:50.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And let me just add, combined
with that, it was very clear
that, related, the president

12:52.133 --> 12:56.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
also made it very clear that he
was very concerned about Russian
aggression and the need to have

12:58.100 --> 13:02.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a cessation of the violence
and the conflict in Ukraine,
as well as in Syria.

13:04.400 --> 13:07.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He talked about Islamic radical
terrorism, and then he also
talked about energy security,

13:09.633 --> 13:14.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
which hasn't gotten a lot of
attention and it's behind me
here at the royal castle where

13:14.500 --> 13:19.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he gave a speech actually before
what's called the Three Seas
Summit, an initiative paid

13:21.566 --> 13:24.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by the Poles, the Croats and
there were 12 countries from
Central Europe that spoke to

13:24.500 --> 13:29.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
this issue about the need
for energy dependents,
energy security and
energy efficiency and

13:31.100 --> 13:33.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the establishment
of an infrastructure
in Central Europe.

13:33.333 --> 13:37.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Karen Donfried, are
those the main messages that
to you have come across from

13:37.633 --> 13:39.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this trip?

13:39.600 --> 13:41.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAREN DONFRIED, FORMER OBAMA
NATIONAL SECURITY COUNCIL STAFF:
There were two things that

13:41.100 --> 13:42.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
struck me about President
Trump's stop in Poland.

13:42.866 --> 13:47.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
One was what a big boost
this was to the current
Polish government.

13:49.866 --> 13:53.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Poland is an overwhelmingly
pro-American country and that's
significant in the context of a

13:55.233 --> 14:00.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
European Union that's been
quite critical of democratic
backsliding in Poland.

14:02.266 --> 14:06.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, the European Commission
has been looking at whether
Poland is staying true to rule

14:06.033 --> 14:09.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of law, independent judiciary,
freedom of the press.

14:09.200 --> 14:12.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, it was very significant
for this Polish government.

14:12.633 --> 14:17.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The second thing that struck
me was the speech he gave
that Paula just referred to.

14:17.000 --> 14:22.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the one hand, had
many elements of the
traditional transatlantic
speech, reaffirming

14:24.533 --> 14:27.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
U.S. commitment to the
Article 5, the collective
defense piece of the NATO
alliance, his support

14:29.933 --> 14:32.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
for strong transatlantic
relationship.

14:32.100 --> 14:37.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But then on the other hand,
you had a dark view of a clash
of civilizations and you had

14:39.100 --> 14:43.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it on your opening clip, the
president's comment about the
West and our ability to stand up

14:43.533 --> 14:45.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to this challenge.

14:45.633 --> 14:50.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And I think some people
are wondering how we in
the U.S. under President
Trump are defining

14:50.833 --> 14:52.466 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
that West.

14:52.466 --> 14:54.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
WOODRUFF: Well, how do
you respond to that,
Paula Dobriansky?

14:54.900 --> 14:59.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Because it did raise, I think,
questions in people's minds
about what is this conflict

14:59.600 --> 15:02.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
as the president sees it?

15:02.300 --> 15:07.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DOBRIANSKY: Well, first, I
think that Karen was right,
the president did highlight the

15:09.266 --> 15:14.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
importance over decades of the
Polish relationship with the
United States and even cited the

15:15.700 --> 15:19.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
roles of such generals,
Kosciuszko and Pilsudski.

15:19.466 --> 15:22.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, our relationship
has mattered greatly.

15:22.600 --> 15:26.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I saw it in a broader
context, though, than
Karen had expressed.

15:26.566 --> 15:28.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I saw it as a bond.

15:28.633 --> 15:33.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And on the other issue,
I saw and looked at the
words that he enunciated.

15:35.133 --> 15:38.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He really spoke a great deal
to freedom, to liberty, to
captive nations, he referred to

15:40.266 --> 15:42.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in his remarks.

15:42.300 --> 15:46.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He did talk about the importance
of values and even towards the
end of the speech expressed

15:48.400 --> 15:51.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
how it's not just only about
military might, but it is also
about the will -- the will

15:53.500 --> 15:58.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
of the people and,
towards that end, I did
not see that as a dark.

16:00.100 --> 16:03.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I saw that as underscoring
the kind of values that
we do hold very dearly.

16:05.633 --> 16:10.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WOODRUFF: So, if he was
stressing the common
values, Karen Donfried,
how then do you read

16:12.300 --> 16:14.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
what the president has said?

16:14.366 --> 16:18.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Because we know it was on his
other trip to Europe where
he withheld a statement about

16:20.733 --> 16:24.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
so-called Article 5, the mutual
commitment to defense among
the NATO countries, but this

16:25.333 --> 16:26.266 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
time he did.

16:26.266 --> 16:28.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I mean, how do you square that?

16:28.333 --> 16:31.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONFRIED: So, on the one hand,
I don't think we would have
been so focused on the more

16:31.766 --> 16:36.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
traditional aspects of
the speech were it not
to the earlier trip
to Europe for a NATO

16:36.466 --> 16:41.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
leaders meeting where the
president did not affirm
U.S. support for Article 5.

16:42.333 --> 16:44.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's why it was significant.

16:44.266 --> 16:47.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But in that transatlantic
context, it was also significant
that he didn't mention the

16:47.566 --> 16:52.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
European Union because
typically, the U.S. has
defined its relationship
with Europe both

16:54.533 --> 16:58.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
through NATO, but also through
U.S. cooperation with this body
that emphasizes cooperation

16:59.700 --> 17:01.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
among Europeans.

17:01.733 --> 17:06.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The second piece I would
mention is, I was struck by the
focus on values but I actually

17:08.133 --> 17:11.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
searched the speech for the
word democracy, and it didn't
appear and that was striking

17:11.933 --> 17:14.000 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to me.

17:14.000 --> 17:16.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And though he did talk about
the importance of rule of law
and freedom of press in the

17:16.966 --> 17:21.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
speech, when you looked at the
press conference he gave with
President Duda, he was asked

17:24.333 --> 17:27.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about the issue of the
press and said -- expressed
his concern about fake
news and the dishonest

17:28.800 --> 17:30.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
media.

17:30.900 --> 17:34.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, it was a bit of a
mixed message I thought
on those issues around
democratic principles.

17:34.700 --> 17:36.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Paula Dobriansky,
what about that?

17:36.700 --> 17:41.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, we know the president's
view toward the press in the
United States has certainly

17:43.500 --> 17:47.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
been a subject of controversy
and a lot of discussion
and debate recently.

17:49.233 --> 17:52.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DOBRIANSKY: Well, I think,
in the speech, which was his
primary platform, in my view,

17:58.266 --> 18:03.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not the press conference but the
primary platform where he had
an opportunity not just to speak

18:05.300 --> 18:09.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to Poland but, as I mentioned,
to the region at large, and
also to set the foundation for

18:11.900 --> 18:15.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
his meetings coming up in
Hamburg and particularly
with President Putin
where he did underscore

18:17.400 --> 18:20.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
this importance, as
I said, of communism.

18:20.900 --> 18:25.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He talked about it, about the
freedoms that were deprived,
the kind of oppression that

18:25.800 --> 18:30.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this region was under and how,
in terms of the present time,
this is a different period.

18:33.366 --> 18:37.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
This is a period where
we do have to reaffirm
these kinds of values.

18:37.900 --> 18:42.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, I saw it in a
broader strategic sense
of setting a foundation
that has applicability

18:44.833 --> 18:48.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to a number of the issues
that we've just mentioned,
not just Poland, the region at

18:48.933 --> 18:51.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
large, but also for Russia.

18:51.433 --> 18:54.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Karen Donfried,
just about 30 seconds here.

18:54.266 --> 18:59.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But how does all this play
into expectation for tomorrow's
meeting between President Trump

19:00.166 --> 19:02.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and President Putin?

19:02.266 --> 19:04.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONFRIED: So, it becomes much
more complicated for President
Trump when he gets -- well,

19:04.233 --> 19:06.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
he is now in
Germany for the G20.

19:06.800 --> 19:11.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Germany context is more
complicated, because you have a
German chancellor who's facing

19:11.566 --> 19:13.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
reelection campaign
in September.

19:13.533 --> 19:17.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She has a public that
is not supportive of
President Trump's policies.

19:17.766 --> 19:22.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She very much values the
relationship with the U.S., so
she wants to try to reach an

19:22.033 --> 19:27.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
agreement with President Trump
while also staying true to her
principle stands on climate

19:27.633 --> 19:28.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and trade.

19:28.900 --> 19:31.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, it will become
very challenging.

19:31.033 --> 19:35.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The meeting with President Putin
will be something everyone will
be watching and it sounds, based

19:35.600 --> 19:39.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on his comments to the press
conference today, that he won't
be raising the issue of Russian

19:39.333 --> 19:40.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
meddling in U.S. elections.

19:40.600 --> 19:42.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
WOODRUFF: Yes.

19:42.600 --> 19:46.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He certainly -- he said,
yes, it may have happened
but it may not have.

19:47.800 --> 19:49.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He said nobody knows for
sure who was behind it.

19:49.766 --> 19:52.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONFRIED: Which was
also a rebuke of U.S.
intelligence, I would say.

19:52.966 --> 19:56.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Karen Donfried, Paula
Dobriansky, we thank you both.

19:56.300 --> 20:01.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DONFRIED: Thank you so much.

20:03.200 --> 20:06.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
